=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex65 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is early, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: early

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.0764
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5480
  pitch_clarity: 19.7401
  inharmonicity: 0.0034
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -1.8204
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 65
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 65 ---
// amplitude determined by amplitude of trigger
{ Trig.ar(Dust.ar(2), 0.2) * FSinOsc.ar(800, 0, 0.4) }.play;
// amplitude always the same.
{ Trig1.ar(Dust.ar(2), 0.2) * FSinOsc.ar(800, 0, 0.4) }.play
